Sentencas: Continuum-level mass and electronic transport through solid oxide cell electrodes, inclusive of ribbed interconnects, are modeled employing analytical solutions of the 2D Laplace equation.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: These analytical solutions describe localized mass and electronic transport phenomena in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes and localized mass transport phenomena in SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: Two-dimensional constriction resistance effects created by reductions in active transport area are shown to significantly increase internal cell resistances by increasing transport path lengths within a cross-sectional region of the cell.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: Furthermore, these effects can alter cell performance with respect to fuel depletion phenomena and create a competition of losses between mass and electronic transport resistances.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: Fuel depletion is shown to occur at a current density lower than the traditionally defined limiting current density.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: An analytical expression for this fuel depletion current density is proposed based upon the models developed.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: The competition between mass transfer and electronic resistance effects arising from solid oxide cell interconnect geometry is also characterized through parametric studies based on a design of experiments (DOEs) approach.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects

Sentencas: These studies demonstrate the benefits of smaller SOFC unit cell geometry.
Titulo: Continuum-level solid oxide electrode constriction resistance effects
